<paragraph id="E33714A535D4E5D771926115815E1829" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5EAB3D61B80317F74ACF622A7554159" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="A91AE0E0020402CDE3E1E5E04A32F14E" authorityName="Torres-Garcia, Gene and Dania Garcia" authorityYear="2022" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Penicillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Penicillium irregulare" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="irregulare">
<emphasis id="CE6F3796054C2EF2F00715B4F0CD7B51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Penicillium irregulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName id="58A73A07324E464635775535AD0D551B" genus="P." lsidName="P. arizonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="arizonense">
<emphasis id="705991BC3C254C25981BC0A746723217" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. arizonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7AF1108AF61403B3DC7BD477AC3EA591" genus="P." lsidName="P. yarmokense" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="yarmokense">
<emphasis id="2B6EEE21C72430BD7E9441F61C56E17C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. yarmokense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="886BE312F018C086318E7DFBEAA97BD7" genus="P." lsidName="P. canescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis id="DF0ECD0A5FEF35F1E3A85EA2667CF524" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. canescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all belonging to series 
<taxonomicName id="5AC935C7BCA6D187BE1337D90E021DAC" genus="P." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="series" series="Canescentia">
<emphasis id="FCCBB73226F17BA358B3707F712BAC79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Canescentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9B7401BEDBD3FB8AC6A10150EAA031AD" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Phylogenetic tree of Penicillium section Canescentia based on ML analysis obtained by RAxML inferred from the combined tub 2, cmdA, ITS, and rpb 2 loci. Branch lengths are proportional to phylogenetic distance. Bootstrap support values / Bayesian posterior probability scores above 70 % / 0.95 are indicated on the nodes. Bold branches indicate bs / pp values 100 / 1. The tree is rooted to P. sacculum CBS 231.61 and P. senticosum CBS 316.67. The name in red is the new species described in this study. T = Ex-type strain." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.86.73861.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640603" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">4</figureCitation>
). Species of this series are characterized by the production of biverticillate conidiophores, that occasionally produce additional branching stages (divaricate), with smooth- or rough-walled stipes (
<bibRefCitation id="560757CC4ECA53E685FAE5D2917F74CF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" author="Houbraken, J" journalOrPublisher="Studies in Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="5 - 169" refId="B39" refString="Houbraken, J, Kocsube, S, Visagie, CM, Yilmaz, N, Wang, XC, Meijer, M, Kraak, B, Hubka, V, Bensch, K, Samson, RA, Frisvad, JC, 2020. Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species. Studies in Mycology 95: 5 - 169, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" title="Classification of Aspergillus, Penicillium, Talaromyces and related genera (Eurotiales): an overview of families, genera, subgenera, sections, series and species." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.simyco.2020.05.002" volume="95" year="2020">Houbraken et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
; Visage et al. 2021). 
<taxonomicName id="0EB0C904B3482954A0B119B549DE3AF1" authorityName="Torres-Garcia, Gene and Dania Garcia" authorityYear="2022" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Penicillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Penicillium irregulare" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="irregulare">
<emphasis id="4CE4318FD944ED983830CCC62FA132CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Penicillium irregulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from its closest relative 
<taxonomicName id="F0E3ACFCB2C9D3DDB3E02AA20C247C4A" genus="P." lsidName="P. arizonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="arizonense">
<emphasis id="F39B68414D65ED87A7CD79EC1E547765" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. arizonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the production of shorter stipes (13-152 
<normalizedToken id="67BC78497830308F5447189706BCD2C9" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
vs 50-400 
<normalizedToken id="E63E683267CCEEF2F3C0AEAE436471F9" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and metulae (7-10 
<normalizedToken id="FFE954409A9F233FE6EE0CE97C355DF3" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
vs. 8-16 
<normalizedToken id="3A5CFB95E2F63D802A4A47B7821A89D1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and colony reverse yellowish to orange, in contrast to brown shades, even red brown to violet brown on YES agar in 
<taxonomicName id="D71C513819C3044E1DB9A9EDA7E9B053" genus="P." lsidName="P. arizonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="arizonense">
<emphasis id="EFB63DE7941B38CF349A71C7F12FEB72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. arizonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="58C476F446C95F691D0FD3FD6B5DFF2F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep35112" author="Grijseels, S" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports - Nature" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="1 - 13" refId="B21" refString="Grijseels, S, Nielsen, JC, Randelovic, M, Nielsen, J, Nielsen, KF, Workman, M, Frisvad, JC, 2016. Penicillium arizonense, a new, genome sequenced fungal species, reveals a high chemical diversity in secreted metabolites. Scientific Reports - Nature 6: 1 - 13, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep35112" title="Penicillium arizonense, a new, genome sequenced fungal species, reveals a high chemical diversity in secreted metabolites." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep35112" volume="6" year="2016">Grijseels et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="F221532ABC3110946782082B1008F006" genus="P." lsidName="P. irregulare" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="irregulare">
<emphasis id="BB726D45F027DDFE60FDA467162718DC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. irregulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was able to grow at 37°C on CYA, but restrictedly (5-10 mm diam. 7 d), while 
<taxonomicName id="293D5B98EDA37FD1BFA70E9B526B3956" genus="P." lsidName="P. arizonense" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="arizonense">
<emphasis id="068555E693FEC340B8A07D64599E1246" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. arizonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not grow at this temperature.
</paragraph>
